notes: Rain interrupted the Zimbabwe innings after 43.1 overs with the score at 206/4. After a 33 minute delay, the target was revised to 244 off 47 overs.

milestones.description: Otieno has scored 3 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for KENYA breaking Chudasama's record
Andy Flower and Guy Whittall's 132-run partnership is ZIM's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 102 between Campbell and Dave Houghton
Chudasama has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (11) for KENYA, going past Aasif Karim
This is the highest match aggregate (493) involving teams Zimbabwe & Kenya in ODIs
